WEBVTT

00:00.875 --> 00:03.086
ANDY: <i>Previously on</i> NYPD Blue.

00:03.670 --> 00:05.422
-What the hell was that?
-African gray parrot.

00:05.630 --> 00:07.507
Sergeant Gibson brought it
in this morning.

00:07.590 --> 00:09.300
Alex was shot to death this morning.

00:09.426 --> 00:12.137
His buddy said he was having an affair
with a girl named Janet.

00:12.303 --> 00:13.513
Your husband know you been stepping out?

00:13.847 --> 00:15.974
-We’re separated.
-The ring says different.

00:16.307 --> 00:18.685
Well, I wear this ’cause he sees me
without it, and he goes off.

00:18.893 --> 00:20.186
-What happened?
-He came home drunk

00:20.353 --> 00:21.604
and started yelling at me.

00:21.813 --> 00:23.940
He went and got a bat
and started breaking things up,

00:24.107 --> 00:25.400
And then he came at me.

00:25.567 --> 00:27.027
If he had his gun on him,
he would've shot me.

00:27.193 --> 00:29.362
Stan Hatcher. The borough’s assigned me
to your squad.

00:29.446 --> 00:30.655
-Effective when?
-Today.

00:30.780 --> 00:32.198
Wilmer, you’re so full of crap,

00:32.323 --> 00:34.534
-it’s no wonder your skin is brown.
-(SPEAKING SPANISH)

00:35.577 --> 00:38.079
-Start talking English, asshole!
-All right, all right, enough!

00:38.163 --> 00:40.206
You need to lay back
and see how this squad works.

00:40.498 --> 00:42.459
Fine, I'd like to fit in
with the team here.

00:42.584 --> 00:44.794
So, how about tomorrow
we make a fresh start?

00:45.086 --> 00:47.672
JOHN: Oh, man.
You are going to hell for this.

00:47.797 --> 00:50.216
It’s always been my hope
that guy got a sense of humor.

00:51.009 --> 00:52.135
MALE VOICE ON TAPE: <i>Douche bag.</i>

00:52.886 --> 00:55.346
<i>Douche bag. Douche bag.</i>

00:55.805 --> 00:58.224
<i>Douche bag. Douche bag.</i>

01:10.320 --> 01:12.655
-Morning, bright eyes. You’re in early.
-Fives.

01:13.198 --> 01:14.991
You’re huggable as a porcupine, Sipowicz,

01:15.075 --> 01:17.869
-but you got an admirable work ethic.
-Thanks, Sarge.

01:19.996 --> 01:23.166
-Permission to board, Colonel.
-Douche bag. (SQUAWKS)

01:24.542 --> 01:27.212
Uh... yeah. I was gonna mention that,
there’s something wrong with your bird.

01:27.337 --> 01:29.005
-COLONEL: Douche bag.
-It’s been saying that

01:29.089 --> 01:30.340
-ever since I got in, loud.
-COLONEL: Douchebag.

01:30.590 --> 01:31.716
I don’t know where
it could've got it from.

01:31.883 --> 01:33.760
-(TELEPHONE RINGS)
-(COLONEL WHISTLING)

01:34.344 --> 01:36.179
Fifteen squad, Sergeant Gibson.

01:36.346 --> 01:39.015
-COLONEL: Douche bag, douche bag.
-Uh... nothing.

01:39.557 --> 01:40.934
(COLONEL WHISTLING) Douche...

01:41.017 --> 01:44.104
That was nothing. Uh-huh.
Thanks, inspector.

01:45.313 --> 01:48.024
DOA 488 Forsyth. I’ll call the others.

01:48.274 --> 01:50.944
Gibson, we’ve got crime victims
that come in here.

01:51.027 --> 01:53.613
Those assholes on night watch,
Boyce and Debrovsky.

01:53.738 --> 01:55.657
They probably sat in here
all night chanting it.

01:55.782 --> 01:57.659
Crime victims on the worst day
of their life,

01:57.992 --> 01:59.744
giving statements of items stolen
from their home

01:59.869 --> 02:02.372
or descriptions of loved ones
that went missing or worse.

02:02.622 --> 02:05.125
They’ve got to be called Douche bag
by a bird,

02:05.208 --> 02:06.376
you don’t think we’ll get complaints?

02:06.668 --> 02:09.337
You know, the voice of that sounds
an awful lot like you, Sipowicz.

02:09.629 --> 02:12.465
-(COLONEL WHISTLING)
-All right, now you’re getting paranoid.

02:13.675 --> 02:16.261
-(TELEPHONE RINGING)
-(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

02:16.469 --> 02:18.096
COLONEL: Douche bag.

02:18.513 --> 02:22.183
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

03:14.903 --> 03:17.322
(THEME MUSIC CONCLUDES)

03:33.171 --> 03:35.506
Helen Stoles, apparent suicide.

03:35.715 --> 03:38.968
-(SIGHS) Young girl, hate to see that.
-(SIREN WAILING)

03:39.177 --> 03:41.012
-ANDY: Who found her?
-STAN: Super.

03:41.179 --> 03:43.389
Her boss stopped by
off her missing two days of work.

03:43.598 --> 03:45.850
-He got the super to open the door.
-Where’s her boss?

03:45.975 --> 03:47.477
I got his statement and kicked him.

03:47.602 --> 03:49.020
-You kicked him?
-STAN: Yeah.

03:49.979 --> 03:52.941
-I got his info. I could get him back.
-(SIGHS)

03:53.775 --> 03:56.027
-Where’d she work?
-Saint Luke’s hospital, nightshift,

03:56.361 --> 03:57.654
clerical job.

03:58.154 --> 03:59.948
Boss say she’d been depressed lately?

04:00.114 --> 04:02.158
He said he hadn’t noticed,
but she was never real talkative.

04:02.367 --> 04:03.826
-How long she work there?
-STAN: One year.

04:04.160 --> 04:05.536
-ANDY: She got family?
-STAN: Not in town.

04:05.745 --> 04:07.580
-ANDY: Boyfriend?
-STAN: He didn’t think so.

04:07.747 --> 04:09.040
-Why?
-STAN: She was a loner?

04:09.332 --> 04:11.709
Want me get the boss back?
I got his home, cell, pager,

04:12.126 --> 04:14.545
height, weight, date of birth,
astrological sign.

04:14.629 --> 04:17.590
When it’s my case, I just generally like
to speak face-to-face

04:17.715 --> 04:19.509
-with people involved.
-Sure.

04:20.760 --> 04:23.680
Uh... start a canvass,
see what the neighbors say?

04:26.057 --> 04:27.058
Later.

04:30.937 --> 04:32.939
Did you see this suicide note
on the counter? It’s a long one.

04:33.982 --> 04:35.525
ANDY: What’s your take on this Hatcher?

04:35.608 --> 04:37.527
If he stays out of my way,
I got no beef with him.

04:38.194 --> 04:39.487
(CLEARS THROAT) The note?

04:41.322 --> 04:44.075
It says she was kidnapped
and held for two months last year.

04:44.242 --> 04:46.452
A guy drugged and raped her,
kept her starving and naked.

04:46.619 --> 04:48.037
She didn’t report it to the police
out of shame,

04:48.204 --> 04:50.790
but she got a partial plate
on the perp’s van.

04:53.209 --> 04:55.670
"I never saw him when he abducted me
or when he let me go,

04:55.795 --> 04:58.464
"and I never got a clear look at his face,
when I was in a basement.

04:58.756 --> 05:00.466
"I was fed through a slot In the door,

05:00.675 --> 05:02.802
"and I would always fall asleep
after I ate.

05:03.094 --> 05:04.804
"When I'd wake up,
It would be hours later,

05:05.013 --> 05:06.472
"and I could tell I’d been raped."

05:07.724 --> 05:10.935
That was the DOA'S stepmother
in Waukegan.

05:11.102 --> 05:13.646
She says she uh...
talked to Helen two weeks ago.

05:14.188 --> 05:15.398
She sounded normal.

05:15.690 --> 05:17.817
Stepmom know anything
about the girl being kidnapped?

05:18.526 --> 05:19.694
First she’d heard of it.

05:19.819 --> 05:22.030
What about going missing
two months last year?

05:22.447 --> 05:25.783
The stepmom said that Helen
was pretty sporadic calling home,

05:25.867 --> 05:27.035
so they wouldn’t have noticed.

05:27.118 --> 05:28.995
DOA. have any history of mental illness?

05:29.203 --> 05:32.373
None, but she did have
a nasty Meth problem in high school.

05:32.540 --> 05:33.875
Two stints in rehab.

05:34.876 --> 05:37.879
(SIGHS) Neighbors said the DOA kept
to herself, no visitors.

05:38.046 --> 05:40.340
Landlord said she missed last July
and August's rent.

05:40.506 --> 05:42.300
Out of the blue she reappeared
and paid up.

05:42.592 --> 05:44.093
She didn’t say nothing
about this to anybody?

05:45.595 --> 05:48.014
Got a hit off the partial plate
in the DOA's note.

05:48.264 --> 05:50.933
So, Dodge van registered
to a Paul Grady, Queens' address.

05:51.392 --> 05:53.603
Wife said he’s at work,
a dry cleaners in Chelsea.

05:53.978 --> 05:55.938
-This Grady got a record?
-Nothing.

05:56.481 --> 05:59.233
Making progress. Ten minutes
he hasn’t mentioned the word,

05:59.317 --> 06:00.902
just a matter of negative conditioning.

06:01.152 --> 06:03.488
So, when if he says the word again,

06:03.988 --> 06:05.990
you got to nail him
with a quick "naughty bird."

06:06.157 --> 06:08.785
Yeah, yeah we’re gonna be running around
like lunatics all day,

06:08.868 --> 06:09.911
yelling "naughty bird."

06:10.703 --> 06:12.330
-We’re grabbing a guy up.
-Who?

06:12.663 --> 06:13.748
I’ll fill you in, Sarge.

06:16.584 --> 06:18.920
I was told downstairs
to speak to a detective.

06:19.921 --> 06:21.339
How can we help you, Ma’am?

06:21.798 --> 06:25.635
Something very dear to me was stolen
and I'm afraid I know who took it.

06:25.968 --> 06:29.972
Oh, uh... come on this way.
Detective Medavoy and Detective Jones.

06:30.348 --> 06:32.350
-Veronica Lewis.
-COLONEL: Douche bag.

06:32.558 --> 06:34.811
-Hmm?
-Just a talking parrot, Ma’am.

06:34.977 --> 06:37.647
Uh... It was mistrained at the pet store.

06:37.814 --> 06:39.065
-Naughty bird!
-(COLONEL WHISTLING)

06:39.524 --> 06:41.234
-(TELEPHONE RINGING)
-(DOOR CLOSING)

06:42.735 --> 06:46.322
I’m a little embarrassed coming here
to air out family laundry.

06:47.490 --> 06:49.242
Well, a family member stole something
from you?

06:49.659 --> 06:52.912
A diamond ring, it was a gift
from my late husband.

06:53.287 --> 06:55.915
-Who is it you think might have taken it?
-My nephew Tim.

06:56.374 --> 06:59.210
He’s staying at my house
in the spare room.

06:59.544 --> 07:01.254
His mother’s in California,

07:01.379 --> 07:04.924
and I'm trying to take care of him
until he gets work.

07:05.800 --> 07:08.553
I... Is your nephew the only one
with access to the apartment?

07:08.719 --> 07:13.975
No, I have a maid and a... a handyman
came through last week, but it’s Tim.

07:14.684 --> 07:16.018
He’s had his struggles.

07:17.061 --> 07:20.773
-Drugs?
-Mainly, but he insists he’s clean. Uh...

07:22.108 --> 07:24.777
-I don’t know.
-Have you talked to him about the ring?

07:24.986 --> 07:26.112
He denies it.

07:26.571 --> 07:29.365
But... my maid has been
with me for 30 years,

07:29.490 --> 07:31.534
my handyman for 20, so...

07:31.742 --> 07:34.620
-Well, we’ll have a conversation with him.
-What if it wasn’t Tim?

07:34.871 --> 07:37.165
I don’t want to alienate him or my sister.

07:38.124 --> 07:42.462
Um... how about we tell your nephew
that you’re not behind the investigation,

07:42.837 --> 07:45.298
that it’s a mandatory requirement
of the insurance company.

07:45.923 --> 07:48.426
Oh, that would be very kind.

07:50.344 --> 07:53.181
Uh... if you don’t mind,
we need you to make out a report.

07:53.431 --> 07:54.724
Of course.

07:57.768 --> 08:00.396
Sit down. This your first time
in a Police Station, Mr. Grady?

08:00.480 --> 08:01.481
Yeah, you bet.

08:01.606 --> 08:03.733
ANDY: Now, we’ll make it painless
as we can.

08:04.692 --> 08:08.279
You drive a blue Dodge van with...

08:08.988 --> 08:11.491
-this license plate right there?
-Yes.

08:11.991 --> 08:13.743
You the main person driving
or other people, too?

08:13.910 --> 08:17.538
Well, Atilio, who works for me,
he drives it sometimes Marcus, also.

08:17.663 --> 08:19.790
Depends on who’s doing the deliveries
on a given day.

08:19.916 --> 08:22.293
We’re a full-service laundry.
So, why do you ask?

08:22.585 --> 08:24.378
You know a woman named Helen Stoles?

08:25.129 --> 08:27.173
-I don’t think so.
-She says she knows you.

08:27.757 --> 08:29.342
I don’t think I’ve ever heard the name.

08:29.634 --> 08:31.135
I’m gonna show you a photograph,
Mr. Grady.

08:31.469 --> 08:32.887
Would you tell me
if you recognize the woman in it?

08:33.930 --> 08:35.681
-Oh, my God.
-(SIREN WAILING)

08:36.390 --> 08:37.975
-TOM: Is that woman dead?
-Yeah.

08:38.559 --> 08:41.103
And we think there’s a possibility
you had contact with her

08:41.187 --> 08:42.188
when she was alive.

08:42.355 --> 08:45.024
If that’s the case, Mr. Grady,
We need to know now.

08:45.316 --> 08:46.651
Study the picture a little more.

08:49.362 --> 08:50.404
You know...

08:51.739 --> 08:55.576
about six months ago this uh...
this disturbed woman came to our door

08:55.660 --> 08:56.911
around two in the morning.

08:57.036 --> 09:01.082
This filthy, dirty, clothes all torn,
glassy-eyed.

09:01.457 --> 09:04.168
-That might be her.
-She came to your door and did what?

09:04.544 --> 09:07.046
Just asked if she could and sit down
and have some water.

09:07.213 --> 09:09.715
-And you let her?
-I thought she had been attacked.

09:09.882 --> 09:12.301
I was gonna call the police,
but then she started screaming

09:12.385 --> 09:15.179
and calling me all kinds of names,
and then she just ran out the door.

09:15.513 --> 09:16.597
Your wife see this woman?

09:16.931 --> 09:18.724
Absolutely, there was no sleeping
through it.

09:18.933 --> 09:20.476
Did you ever call the police that night?

09:21.269 --> 09:23.729
I just wanted her out
and the door locked behind her.

09:24.313 --> 09:27.191
I guess I should have,
especially if that’s her in the photo.

09:29.318 --> 09:31.028
Would you mind sticking around
for a little bit?

09:31.529 --> 09:33.406
-We need to check a few things out.
-Okay.

09:40.788 --> 09:42.957
Tim Lewis? Detectives Jones and Medavoy.

09:43.124 --> 09:44.500
-Mind if we come in?
-About?

09:44.584 --> 09:47.795
Your aunt’s missing ring.
She’s making an insurance claim.

09:47.920 --> 09:50.089
She needs a police report uh...
with interviews.

09:50.965 --> 09:51.966
Right.

09:53.050 --> 09:55.511
All right... come on in.

09:57.138 --> 09:58.723
You know anything
about how the ring went missing?

09:58.848 --> 10:00.516
Like I told her, I don’t.

10:01.392 --> 10:04.312
You uh... have a criminal record, Tim?

10:04.770 --> 10:07.732
-I’ll bet you know that I do.
-Yeah, possession and sales.

10:08.691 --> 10:11.611
-You been getting high lately?
-Not in nine months.

10:11.902 --> 10:13.779
You willing to take a urine test
to prove it?

10:13.988 --> 10:17.158
Sure, but before you go wading
through my whiz,

10:17.450 --> 10:19.493
did my aunt tell you
about the little trip to mars

10:19.577 --> 10:21.203
she’s been on for the last six months?

10:21.912 --> 10:23.164
What does that mean?

10:23.831 --> 10:26.917
My uncle died, like, five years ago
and since then,

10:27.001 --> 10:29.629
she’s made some pretty dramatic
lifestyle changes,

10:29.920 --> 10:31.964
and as far as the dangers concerned
with those changes,

10:32.048 --> 10:35.551
like getting ripped off...
she’s neck deep in denial.

10:36.010 --> 10:38.137
That’s the personal ad she took out.

10:38.804 --> 10:43.017
"Autumn spirit, sexually liberated,
seeks partners, any age."

10:43.684 --> 10:45.603
From the traffic in
and out of her bedroom,

10:45.728 --> 10:46.854
she’s had a lot of response.

10:47.146 --> 10:49.815
And any guy answering an ad
to bang a broad her age

10:49.982 --> 10:51.484
doesn’t exactly make him high quality.

10:52.234 --> 10:54.945
-You get any names?
-I don’t know if she does.

10:55.446 --> 10:57.990
-Exactly how old is your aunt?
-Late 60s.

10:58.366 --> 10:59.909
And I'm all for her little rebirth,

10:59.992 --> 11:01.827
but she can’t accuse me
of stealing something

11:01.911 --> 11:04.664
-50 other guys had access to.
-Fifty guys?

11:04.872 --> 11:06.749
Maybe, more than 50.
Honestly, I lost count.

11:07.124 --> 11:09.710
You want to find out
who took the ring, talk to them.

11:10.461 --> 11:12.797
BALDWIN: All right, we’ll be in touch.

11:19.095 --> 11:20.221
EDDIE: Pretty bird.

11:20.596 --> 11:22.431
-Pretty bird.
-(TELEPHONE RINGING)

11:22.723 --> 11:23.808
Pretty bird.

11:24.517 --> 11:26.686
All right, all right, thanks, Mrs. Grady.

11:28.187 --> 11:29.772
She confirms what her husband said.

11:29.939 --> 11:32.525
Girl showed up at two in the morning,
freaked out, same story down the line.

11:33.067 --> 11:35.569
Maybe our uh... DOA.
was drugged out, delusional,

11:35.903 --> 11:37.947
made up the thing
about Grady's license plate,

11:38.114 --> 11:39.532
off seeing the uh...

11:39.949 --> 11:41.992
-the van in his uh, driveway...
-Pretty bird.

11:42.076 --> 11:43.828
...when she knocked
On his door that night.

11:44.203 --> 11:45.538
-(SCOFFS)
-EDDIE: Pretty bird.

11:45.621 --> 11:46.664
Our DOA I’m talking about.

11:46.997 --> 11:49.041
Yeah, I heard you. Maybe she made it up.

11:49.375 --> 11:51.293
-It’s still pretty elaborate.
-STAN: Thank you.

11:51.377 --> 11:52.461
EDDIE: Pretty bird.

11:53.129 --> 11:55.131
I got something might be worth
looking into.

11:55.214 --> 11:57.383
A girl named Gina Belle
reported being abducted

11:57.508 --> 11:59.969
off Orange Street in Brooklyn Heights
two years ago.

12:00.136 --> 12:02.763
-Case is still active.
-She got abducted? That it?

12:02.847 --> 12:05.599
Well, she said she was held
for a few weeks, drugged, raped.

12:05.808 --> 12:07.518
-She lives on Clinton.
-(TELEPHONE RINGING)

12:07.852 --> 12:11.147
-JOHN: We’ll get her in.
-Maybe uh... Rita and me could.

12:11.313 --> 12:12.523
We got it.

12:13.774 --> 12:16.652
(CLEARS THROAT) But widen out the net
to Jersey and Connecticut.

12:16.777 --> 12:19.071
Anything pops with a similar M.O.,
it’s all yours.

12:19.405 --> 12:21.699
-Done.
-EDDIE: Pretty bird.

12:21.907 --> 12:24.118
-(COLONEL GURGLING)
-Pretty bird.

12:24.368 --> 12:26.412
-EDDIE: Pretty bird.
-We’re leaving again, we’ll be back.

12:27.830 --> 12:29.915
(COLONEL SQUAWKING)

12:40.760 --> 12:41.927
Have a seat, Miss Belle.

12:43.012 --> 12:45.264
Can I ask why you’re looking
into my case now?

12:45.723 --> 12:47.892
-So long after it happened?
-We found similar circumstances

12:48.100 --> 12:49.226
in another case.

12:49.310 --> 12:50.770
-Another girl?
-ANDY: It’s possible.

12:50.936 --> 12:52.855
We need to hear what happened
to you to be sure.

12:53.022 --> 12:55.274
Your report said you were abducted
in Brooklyn?

12:55.941 --> 12:58.152
I worked for a printing company.

12:58.277 --> 13:01.697
Walking home,
a car pulled up next to me.

13:01.947 --> 13:06.285
I really didn’t even notice it,
and then there was a wet rag over my face

13:06.535 --> 13:09.163
that smelled sort of sweet.

13:09.538 --> 13:11.290
And I woke up in a dark room.

13:11.457 --> 13:13.417
-Did you see the man who grabbed you?
-No.

13:14.043 --> 13:15.461
JOHN: Do you remember
what kind of car he drove?

13:15.836 --> 13:17.004
I never really saw it.

13:17.129 --> 13:19.048
Can you describe the room
that you were held in?

13:19.131 --> 13:21.342
It was a long time ago, dark...

13:22.426 --> 13:25.679
concrete floor, I just can’t think
of anything else.

13:25.930 --> 13:27.598
When you were picked up by the police,

13:27.681 --> 13:29.725
you told them you were held
for at least two weeks.

13:29.892 --> 13:32.520
Right, but I was a little panicked,
I think.

13:32.645 --> 13:35.773
I... I’m embarrassed to say it,
but I may have exaggerated.

13:35.898 --> 13:38.359
-So, it was more like...
-Two days maybe.

13:38.484 --> 13:41.779
-Were you sexually assaulted?
-I don’t think so, no.

13:42.279 --> 13:44.365
Your rape kit indicated you were.

13:44.573 --> 13:45.991
Well, if it did happen,

13:46.492 --> 13:48.869
It must’ve been when I was asleep,
drugged.

13:49.036 --> 13:51.205
But I don’t remember any kind
of sexual assault.

13:51.413 --> 13:52.957
You remember being picked up
by the police?

13:53.207 --> 13:58.712
I woke up in an alley,
and I just, sort of, got up

13:58.838 --> 14:00.881
and found someone to call a cop.

14:01.048 --> 14:03.384
Police report said
you were found wandering naked,

14:03.592 --> 14:06.762
-disoriented.
-Right. That’s right.

14:07.555 --> 14:09.223
I’m not trying to downplay what happened.

14:09.682 --> 14:12.810
Because it was a scary experience,
